    "created_at": "2015-01-30T03:36:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-30T03:38:17Z",
    "body": "It's possible to create a .pkg that does not install any files but only runs preinstall/postinstall scripts by passing in `--nopayload` to `pkgbuild` (and specifying the install scripts with `--scripts`). You can try that technique to make a separate uninstaller .pkg that simply runs an uninstall script as a postinstall script, that way OS X users can uninstall rust in a way similar to how they installed it.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
